You didn&#39;t say what Markdown processor that you are using. Basic Markdown does not have the ability to provide context in the markup that could inform CSS styles. Some variations of Markdown might support an enhancement that could lead to a usable solution.

Without changing processors, your best bet would be to post-process the HTML to include enough styling information to achieve what you want. It could be as simple as adding a class to a specific page&#39;s `&lt;body&gt;` tag. Then you could add a style like:

