The TypeScript may be improved this way, to be more idiomatic IMO:

- Favor parameter properties to have terser code for classes
- Skip the `public` keyword since it&#39;s implicit but in constructor for parameter properties.
- Prefer `readonly` fields when possible to favor immutability

```ts
type TestMethodName = &quot;fly&quot; | &quot;swim&quot;| &quot;drive&quot;;

class Wrapper {
  readonly name = &quot;event&quot;;

  constructor(readonly test: Test) {}

  addListener(method: TestMethodName, listener: Function) {
    this.test[method](this.name, listener);
  }
}

```

